uk.ac.susx.mlcl.byblo.enumerators
Interface Enumerator<T>

Type Parameters:
T - type of object being indexed.
All Superinterfaces:
Iterable<Map.Entry<Integer,T>>
All Known Implementing Classes:
BiMapEnumerator, JDBMStringEnumerator, MemoryBasedStringEnumerator, NullEnumerator
public interface Enumerator<T>
extends Iterable<Map.Entry<Integer,T>>

Interface defining a unique indexing of complex objects (usually strings). Implementations of this interface are expected to associate each unique object with an integer value. When an object is queried using indexOf for the first time a new unique integer is returned. On subsequent queries of of the same object, the same unique integer will be returned. After an object has been assigned a unique id it can be retrieved using the valueOf method.

Author:
Hamish I A Morgan <hamish.morgan@sussex.ac.uk>
